<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-07T03:43:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-07T03:43:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/725</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Curtis</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-07T08:00:00-00:43">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1916, 8 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Cargo steamer expected very soon will provide sufficient revenue to pay
                            June interest and to set aside funds for July interest. Do bankers
                            consider July interest to be suspended under notice from Liberian
                            Government referred to in Department’s June 5, 4 p.m.?</p>
                        <p>Agreement drawn but not executed between Bank of British West Africa and
                            Liberian Government calling for loan of nine thousand dollars monthly to
                            the Liberian Government for its running expenses secured by all revenues
                            not assigned. Tentative agreement supported by Clark and Worley. What is
                            the view of the Department and bankers?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>